      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Pursuant to the mayors request,\nthe council last night appointed\nCouncilmen Phillips, Baldwin and\nBrown to represent it at the in\nvestigation of the Howard street\nbridge collapse, and today the\nmayor appointed as the representa-\ntives of the citizens the following:\n\n\nF. E. Goodall, chamber of COM\nmerce; Fred Phair, contractor:\nHenry Rising, the press; George e.\nMiller, Central Labor Union; F. P.\nHogan, real estate; E. H. Jameson,\ntaxpayers league.\n\n\nThe date of investigation has not\nyet been set.\n\n\nThis afternoon representatives Of\nthe chamber of commerce and the\ncity council are meeting in the\ncommittee rooms of the council\nand discussing the question Of the\ncollapse of the bridge."
    }
  ]
